rofile.", "universalIdentifier": "5e0a9d2c-0301-4d01-8d01-1d5f8e3c7e01"}, "VEXA_API_BASE": {"value": "https://api.cloud.vexa.ai", "isSecret": false, "description": "Vexa API base URL. Cloud users: leave as default. Self-host: e.g. https://api.your-vexa.example.", "universalIdentifier": "5e0a9d2c-0302-4d02-8d02-1d5f8e3c7e02"}, "TWENTY_API_KEY": {"isSecret": true, "description": "Temporary workaround. Paste a workspace API key (Settings → APIs & Webhooks, role: Admin). Why: Twenty 2.2 backend logic functions cannot authenticate to /graphql — the runtime-injected APPLICATION_ACCESS token is rejected and the SDK's refresh path requires a browser. Tracked at github.com/twentyhq/twenty/issues/20423. Drop this variable once the platform supports backend app auth.", "universalIdentifier": "5e0a9d2c-0304-4d04-8d04-1d5f8e3c7e04"}, "VEXA_DASHBOARD_BASE": {"value": "https://dashboard.vexa.ai", "isSecret": false, "description": "Vexa dashboard base URL (used for vexa_url deep links). Cloud users: leave as default.", "universalIdentifier": "5e0a9d2c-0303-4d03-8d03-1d5f8e3c7e03"}, "VEXA_WEBHOOK_SECRET": {"isSecret": true, "description": "Optional. Shared HMAC secret for Vexa → Twenty webhook delivery. Generate a strong random string (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`) and paste here. When set, the cron tells Vexa to POST status updates to https://<your-twenty>/s/vexa-webhook signed with this secret, and Twenty reconciles Call rows in near-real-time instead of waiting for the next cron tick. Leave empty to keep cron-only polling.", "universalIdentifier": "e4988e27-c3d2-4423-ad32-6ba53e2d4423"}}, "defaultRoleUniversalIdentifier": "c7300aee-e3a7-45e1-9a31-2714eb93f6bf"}, "pageLayouts": [], "publicAssets": [], "logicFunctions": [{"name": "vexa-cron-dispatch", "description": "Every minute: mirror calendar (last 90d + future) into Calls and dispatch Vexa bots for eligible upcoming meetings.", "handlerName": "default.config.handler", "timeoutSeconds": 120, "builtHandlerPath": "src/logic-functi